When talking about an expensive activity that I truly enjoy, I would say it's travelling. When I'm a bit stressed out because of
hectic life in the city, I sometimes go on an excursion to explore new places. It really helps me refresh my mind, gain new exposures
to other cultures, and broaden my perspective.
I often travel by myself. Before any journeys, I have to make sure that I'm well-prepared. I use google to know more about the destination like it's tourist attractions, speciality food, and especially the hospitality of the local people. I know I will be happier in a place where I am welcomed. I also have to prepare necessary items such as my identification, insurance, first-aid, etc.. In order to save money for exploration, I often determine to stay in hostel.
As you can see, there are many things that I have to prepare to ensure a smooth travelling experience. But I do love the feeling of autonomy, and the novel experiences that I gain throughout my journeys. 
